{"title": "Regulation of parathyroid hormone secretion: proportional control by calcium, lack of effect of phosphate", "url": "https://academic.oup.com/endo/article-abstract/83/5/1043/2695784", "author": "LM Sherwood and GP Mayer and CF Ramberg Jr\u2026", "abstract": "Measurement by radioimmunoassay of secretory rates for parathyroid hormone in the cow shows that hypocalcemia is the major stimulus for hormone production; hypercalcemia quickly abolishes secretion. Phosphate causes no direct effect on secretion of the hormone \u2026"}